# Command skopeo

## What does this command do:

Work with remote images registries - retrieving information, images, signing content

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: sudo dnf install skopeo
For Raspberry Pi install using: sudo apt install skopeo
For Mac install using: brew install skopeo

## Command path

For Fedora run: /usr/bin/skopeo
For Raspberry Pi run: /usr/bin/skopeo
For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/skopeo

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/containers/skopeo

## Command options

# Global flags
skopeo --debug                          # enable debug output
skopeo --insecure-policy                # skip trust policy checks
skopeo --override-arch ARCH             # override CPU architecture for image selection
skopeo --override-os OS                 # override OS for image selection
skopeo --command-timeout 30s            # timeout for the command execution

# inspect — show image metadata from a registry
skopeo inspect docker://docker.io/library/alpine
skopeo inspect --config docker://docker.io/library/alpine          # show image config (env, entrypoint, etc.)
skopeo inspect --raw docker://docker.io/library/alpine             # show raw manifest
skopeo inspect --no-tags docker://docker.io/library/alpine         # omit tag list
skopeo inspect -f "{{.Digest}}" docker://docker.io/library/alpine  # format output with Go template
skopeo inspect --creds USER:PASS docker://registry.example.com/img

# list-tags — list all tags for a repository
skopeo list-tags docker://docker.io/library/alpine
skopeo list-tags --creds USER:PASS docker://registry.example.com/repo

# copy — copy an image between registries/transports
skopeo copy docker://quay.io/skopeo/stable:latest docker://registry.example.com/skopeo:latest
skopeo copy -a docker://docker.io/library/alpine docker://registry.example.com/alpine  # copy all archs
skopeo copy docker://docker.io/library/alpine dir:/tmp/alpine-dir                      # save to local dir
skopeo copy docker://docker.io/library/alpine docker-archive:/tmp/alpine.tar           # save as tar
skopeo copy --dest-creds USER:PASS docker://src.example.com/img docker://dst.example.com/img
skopeo copy --digestfile /tmp/digest.txt docker://src/img docker://dst/img             # write digest to file

# sync — mirror images from one location to another
skopeo sync --src docker --dest dir registry.example.com/busybox /media/usb
skopeo sync --src docker --dest docker --scoped registry.example.com/myapp registry.internal.com
skopeo sync --src yaml --dest docker sync-manifest.yaml registry.example.com           # use YAML manifest
skopeo sync --dry-run --src docker --dest dir registry.example.com/myapp /tmp/mirror   # preview only

# delete — remove an image from a registry
skopeo delete docker://registry.example.com/myimage:tag
skopeo delete --creds USER:PASS docker://registry.example.com/myimage:tag

# login / logout — authenticate with a registry
skopeo login registry.example.com
skopeo login -u myuser -p mypass registry.example.com
skopeo logout registry.example.com

# manifest-digest — compute the digest of a local manifest file
skopeo manifest-digest /tmp/manifest.json

# standalone-sign / standalone-verify — sign/verify using local keys (sigstore)
skopeo generate-sigstore-key --output-prefix mykey
skopeo standalone-sign manifest.json docker.io/myimage:tag mykey.private --output sig.json
skopeo standalone-verify manifest.json docker.io/myimage:tag mykey.pub sig.json

# Transport prefixes used in IMAGE-NAME arguments
#   docker://          — remote registry (docker v2)
#   docker-archive:    — local .tar file (docker save format)
#   docker-daemon:     — running docker daemon
#   containers-storage: — local containers/storage (podman, buildah)
#   dir:               — local directory (OCI-like layout)
#   oci:               — local OCI image layout directory
#   oci-archive:       — local OCI image layout tar
